# Dallas Rangemaster treble booster — netlist source of truth.
#
# Traced from the Fuzz Dog Range Master schematic (pedalparts.co.uk, NPN-converted layout of
# the original) and cross-checked against diy-fever and ElectroSmash notes. The original is
# PNP germanium (OC44) with a positive-ground -9V supply; values below are the signal-path
# components, polarity handled as a final inversion. See rangemaster-reference.md for the
# stage-by-stage ground truth.
#
# circuitc/netlist.py (RangemasterCircuit) provides these values to the discretizer. Node 0
# is ground (the +4.5/-9 rails are AC ground). Pot wipers split as Rpot1/Rpot2.
#
# === guitar source model (modeled as table axes; not part of the pedal) ===
# Pickup EMF -> Rp + Lp (pickup, morph axis single-coil..humbucker) -> guitar volume pot
# (250k..500k, audio taper, axis) -> cable capacitance to ground (200p..1n, axis) -> jack.
#
# === single-stage germanium booster (MODELED) ===
C1     in     b       4.7n      # input cap; against the low Zin this IS the treble booster
R1     vcc    b       470k      # base bias divider, top
R2     b      0       68k       # base bias divider, bottom
Q1     b      e       c   OC44  # germanium PNP, hFE ~75-100, low leakage selected
Re     e      0       3.9k
Ce     e      0       47u       # emitter bypass (shelf corner ~30 Hz)
RL     vcc    c       10k       # BOOST pot full track = DC collector load (10KA)
# wiper taps the track at fraction b; C4 couples the tap to the output
C4     w      out     10n
Rnext  out    0       1M        # downstream amplifier input (typical)
